This paper discusses dependencies in database design and query optimization, which are core topics in computer science databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a set of axioms for order dependencies, which involves logical reasoning and inference rules, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses theorems and proofs, which are related to cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
